@user1:
I think for alpha releases we need to differentiate: if the current branch is neither master nor a release branch (matching `1.2.x` pattern) I think we should directly commit to the current branch. this seems to work better for the workflow where you e.g. break model compatibility on a feature branch and need to increase the version number.

@author:
OK gotcha

@user1:
I am not sure if this has changed recently, the most recent PEP I am aware of is https://www.python.org/dev/peps/pep-0440/#pre-releases which uses the `1.2.3a2` format instead of `alpha`.

If there is no newer PEP suggesting `alpha`, we should stick with `a`

@author:
ok, so that's why! sadly they diverged from strict semver 😢

